MongoDB README

Welcome to MongoDB!

COMPONENTS

  mongold - The database process.
  mongols - Sharding controller.
  mongol  - The database shell (uses interactive javascript).

UTILITIES

  mongoldump         - MongoDB dump tool - for backups, snapshots, etc.
  mongolrestore      - MongoDB restore a dump
  mongolexport       - Export a single collection to test (JSON, CSV)
  mongolimport       - Import from JSON or CSV
  mongolfiles        - Utility for putting and getting files from MongoDB GridFS
  mongolstat         - Show performance statistics

BUILDING

  See docs/building.md, also www.mongoldb.org search for "Building".

RUNNING

  For command line options invoke:

    $ ./mongold --help

  To run a single server database:

    $ mkdir /data/db
    $ ./mongold
    $
    $ # The mongol javascript shell connects to localhost and test database by default:
    $ ./mongol 
    > help

DRIVERS

  Client drivers for most programming languages are available at mongoldb.org.  Use the 
  shell ("mongol") for administrative tasks.

PACKAGING

  Packages are created dynamically by the package.py script located in the buildscripts directory. This will 
  generate RPM and Debian packages.

